rdf:Description.ns3:ecology: A plant may produce thousands of fruits, most of which are eaten by birds. Privet is used as a food plant by the larvae of some Lepidoptera species including the common emerald , common marbled carpet , copper underwing, engrailed , mottled beauty , scalloped hazel , small angle shades, v-pug , privet hawk moth and willow beauty .
